subject: Re: It's white?
author: tim_woolworth
full_text:
Frank,

I do not hear the crossing over line you heard.  Instead, this appears to be a lengthy conversation.   I am particularly fond of this clip because it is an excellent example of how individual words are selectively used by the others to create long sentences of communication.  This entire clip is one conversation that is cut off at the end.  Do you know a Johnny?
 
What I hear:

@.01 - .05: This is getting a little old for Johnny (male)
@.05: Yeah (male)
@.06: What! (male)
@.07: Uh oh. (male)
@.08: We (male)
@.09: Never (male)
@.09 - .10: Feel the thing is that (male)
@.11: Wasting our time (female)
@.12: What? (electronic)
@.13 - .14: You (?pick up? make them?) sleep 
@.15: the word is cut off.

Tim
